Great Barrier Reef Education Experience Program
Eye on the reef
Explore the beauty of the islands during this multi-day Whitsundays sailing charter on Avatar, the only Trimaran in the Islands.
May 1 - Sept 1
2 days, 2 nights
Every Tuesday, Thursday & Saturday at 11 a.m.
Thursday, Saturday, Monday at 9.30 a.m.
26 guests and 3 fun filled crew!
An Epic Whitsundays Itinerary
, feeling the wind in your hair as
glides effortlessly over turquoise waters. Visit the
, where you’ll walk on
and hike to the
iconic Hill Inlet Lookout
for a jaw-dropping aerial view of the swirling sands below.
Hook Island, Hayman Island, Border Island, and Whitsunday Island
, potentially stopping at some of the
following snorkeling sites in the region
Luncheon Bay, Caves Cove, and Blue Pearl Bay
—plus secret locations the crew will select based on conditions. Swim among
giant clams, tropical fish, and sea turtles
, and immerse yourself in the untouched beauty of the Great Barrier Reef’s
Fast-Paced Sailing or Pure Relaxation—You Choose!
For those who love
help hoist the sails, and experience the thrill of real sailing
as Avatar cuts through the water with unmatched speed. Or, if relaxation is more your style, stretch out on the
, soak up the sun, and take in the breathtaking island views.
Incredible Nights Under the Stars
When the sun sets, the magic continues. Avatar’s
attract marine life for a
unique after-dark viewing experience
, while above deck, the
some of the best stargazing on the planet
. Watch the Milky Way stretch across the night sky, free from city lights, as the waves gently lap against the hull.
Delicious Meals & Social Vibes
Fuel your adventure with
, with favorites like
spaghetti bolognese, beef tacos, fresh meats, crisp salads, homemade bread, dips, crackers, and plenty more
. Dietary requirements? No worries—
all dietaries are catered for
great food, good company, and the best sailing playlist in the Whitsundays
as you make lifelong friends with fellow adventurers.
The tour is estimated to return between
on the final day, but times may vary due to
weather, tides, and tendering logistics
Open Dorm Style Bedding –  Share Singles & doubles
Alcohol, snacks (chips, chocolate, coke, etc.)
Whether you’re looking forward to snorkelling the Great Barrier Reef or simply soaking up the sun on the sands of Whitehaven or Airlie Beach, OzSail can make it happen. Once your holiday plans are made, you’ll want to be sure your departure information is accurate and up-to-date. We can help.
All of our vessels leave from Coral Sea Marina (Meeting Point C) under the umbrellas on the right-hand-side of the two buildings.
Our departure times for Mandrake and Avatar are typically the same:
No large backpacks or suitcases are allowed on-board our vessels. Please only bring bags the same size as an airline carry-on.
Most hostel/hotels in Airlie beach have bag storage facilities for bigger bags.
There is NO bag storage at the marina and you face missing your departure if you bring bags that are not allowed.
In a small soft bag (enviro safe), we suggest that you bring the following:
Travel voucher from your booking agent.
Light clothing/warm clothing in cooler months (May – September)
Sunscreen (30+ highly recommended)
Bath towel and beach towel
Alcohol (no glass please): NO MORE THAN 24 cans of beer OR 4 ltrs cask wine OR 1 ltr spirits.
Glass bottles or red wine.
Sleeping bags or pillows.
Passport or important travel documents
Shampoo and conditioner (for environmental purposes)
Plastic bags (they kill our wildlife and smother our coral)
OzSail is not responsible for any property you take on board the vessel. In particular, we strongly encourage you to take waterproof cameras rather than expensive digital cameras. Your electrical equipment will be ruined if it comes in conta
